block page_headliner
    .container
        .row
            .col-xs-12
                h4.page-description= t('research.headline')
block content
    section#research(data-ng-controller='ResearchController')
        .container
            .row
                .hidden-xs.col-md-3.mt20
                    v-accordion#r-accordion.vAccordion--default(control='accordion')
                        v-pane(id='{{pane.id}}', ng-repeat='pane in panes')
                            v-pane-header
                                //| {{pane.header}}
                                a(href='{{pane.id}}') {{pane.header}}
                            v-pane-content
                                //| {{pane.content}}
                                div(ng-repeat= 'content in pane.contents')
                                    a(href='{{content.link}}') {{content.name}}

                .col-xs-12.col-md-9.research-info
                    //  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Profile
                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    section#Profile
                        .row
                            .col-xs-12
                                h2 My Profile

                        .row
                            .col-xs-12
                                p
                                    strong ニコール·ノボレスの2017年文部科学省研究奨学金の情報ホームページ
                                    br
                                    | お忙しい中、当ホームページをご覧いただき、ありがとうございます。
                                    br
                                    | もしご質問等がございましたら、是非ご連絡ください。<
                                    a(href='mailto:me@shecodez.com')  me@shecodez.com
                                    |  >
                            .col-xs-12.col-md-3
                                img.img-responsive(src='../images/logo.png')
                            .col-xs-12.col-md-8
                                p
                                    strong 自己紹介
                                    br
                                    | 名前: ニコール·ノボレス (Nicole Nobles)
                                    br
                                    | 生年月日: 1990年 7月 5日
                                    br
                                    | 専門分野: コンピュータサイエンス
                                    br
                                    | 趣味: (アメリカでは) ビデオゲーム、趣味のロボット & (日本で) 墨絵、弓道、スノーボード
                            .col-xs-12
                                p.text-justify
                                    strong ロボット工学者を学びたい理由:
                                    |  My goal is to one day put to use the software and hardware knowledge I have acquired over the years
                                    | to build and program a robust and efficient humanoid robot with advanced Artificial Intelligence using
                                    | the latest advances in artificial neural networks. I admire Japan's funding and research that promotes
                                    | the pursuit of knowledge, internationalization, and culture. Japan's university robotics labs are bar none
                                    | and historically serious about robotics, especially humanoid ones, and so I know I will be learning from
                                    | the absolute best in the field.

                    //  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Current Research
                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    section#CurrentResearch
                        .row
                            .col-xs-12
                                h2 Current Research

                        .row
                            .col-xs-12
                                h4#Title Title
                                p
                                    strong The Economy of Cursorial Motion
                                    br
                                    | How the placement of leg joints in a bipedal humanoid affect the mechanical cost of generating force
                                br

                                h4#Abstract Abstract
                                p.text-justify
                                    | Over the past couple of decades, a number of humanoid robots have been designed, and realized: Boston Dynamics'
                                    | Petman, and Atlas Unplugged, Honda's Asimo, the RobotCub Consortium's iCub and Aldebaran Robotics' Nao just to
                                    | name a few. However, all these robots follow the same biomimetics inspired humanoid bipedal plantigrade leg model
                                    | design. This research aims to design and realize a 3D printed humanoid bipedal digitigrade robot with an open source
                                    | machine learning-based controller. With machine learning, we have the potential to develop autonomous, adaptive, and
                                    | robust intelligent machines. With the commercialization of 3D printers and the wide adoption of open source software as
                                    | a development platform, we make it available to all robotics hobbyist of many different backgrounds, countries, and skill levels.
                                    | It is from the array of different backgrounds that we get a plethora of unique robot designs, straight from the imagination,
                                    | that keeps robotics relevant, interesting and ever-evolving.
                                br

                                h4#Design Design Overview
                                p Images coming soon...
                    //  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Field of Study
                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    section#FieldOfStudy
                        .row
                            .col-xs-12
                                h2 Field of Study

                        .row
                            .col-xs-12
                                p.text-justify
                                    | Digitigrade and unguligrade postures improve locomotor economy by increasing stride length.
                                    | (Myers, P., R. Espinosa, C. S. Parr, T. Jones, G. S. Hammond, and T. A. Dewey, 2016)
                                    | If this applies to nature it should also have application in robot design.
                                    strong  My hypothesis is that a bipedal humanoid robot with digitigrade legs will have increased stable step length over
                                        | currently available bipedal humanoid robots with plantigrade foot posture.
                                    |  If this hypothesis is true, it would give this robot increased efficiency of motion making the mechanical cost of generating
                                    | force more economical than existing robots of similar size and weight. This approach to the leg design of a humanoid bipedal
                                    | robot is quite unconventional thus there is little research on the topic.

                                p 現在の専攻分野 (英語):
                                    a(href='downloads/mext/field_of_study.pdf')  www.shecodez.com/field_of_study.pdf
                                    |  [PDF ファイルサイズ : 186KB]
